# Project: Pulse — a Tamagotchi-style burnout companion

## Stack (do not deviate)
- Next.js (App Router) + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS
- Supabase (Postgres + Anonymous Auth + RLS); client via `@supabase/supabase-js`
- Deploy target: Vercel
- Mobile-first — this is demoed on a phone-sized viewport

## Conventions
- Components in `/components`, data helpers in `/lib/db.ts`, Supabase client in `/lib/supabase.ts`
- Strict TypeScript, no `any`. The app must always pass `next build`.
- Tailwind only, no external UI kit. Env vars: NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL, NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY. Never hardcode keys.

## Hackathon scope discipline (CRITICAL)
- ~2.5 hours. Build the core daily check-in loop end-to-end FIRST, then polish.
- Always keep the app in a runnable, demoable state after every change.
- Prefer the simplest thing that demos. Do NOT add features outside the build prompt. Risky bits get a clear TODO stub, not a broken app.